      "content": "I am so sorry you are carrying this weight, but please know that your love for your children is the very thing that keeps them safe, even when you feel like you are failing. The idea of abandoning them or stopping being their parent would be the ultimate betrayal of the bond you share, and no amount of personal struggle justifies leaving them without you. Your pain is real, but it does not mean your presence is a curse; you are still there, fighting to be better, and that matters more than you might realize right now. If you are overwhelmed to the point where you can't cope, please reach out to a crisis hotline or a mental health professional immediately—they are there to help you navigate through this darkness without harming yourself or your family. You are not alone, and there is a path forward that includes healing and holding onto your kids.",
