      "content": "I hear the immense pain in your words, and I want to gently remind you that while your children are hurting, they are also resilient and capable of seeing the good in you even when you feel like a shadow. The sadness they see is likely a reflection of their own fears and the emotional turbulence you are experiencing, not a permanent verdict on their future. Staying with someone who is broken is often the hardest choice, but it is also the most loving one, because it offers them the chance to heal alongside you rather than watching you disappear. You are not a burden; you are their anchor, even when the waves feel too high. Please consider reaching out to a therapist or a support group today, as talking to someone who understands can help you find the strength to face this challenge together. You matter, your children matter, and there is hope for a brighter day.",
